Part D: Multi-Step Word Problems

A tank holds 18.75 gallons of water. It loses 0.48 gallons every hour. How much water remains after 7 hours?

A chef buys 6 packages of cheese that each weigh 1.75 pounds. If a recipe uses 8.4 pounds, how much cheese is left?

A cyclist traveled 153.6 miles over 4 days, riding the same distance each day. How many miles did they ride per day?

A store has 245.25 pounds of candy. They divide it equally into bags weighing 0.75 pounds each. How many bags can they fill?

Part E: Challenge Problems

Explain your reasoning.

A number is multiplied by 0.1. Describe exactly how the digits change.

Why does dividing by 0.01 make a number 100 times larger? Give your own example.